---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";

const clientSnippet = `import { WompiClient } from "@pulgueta/wompi";

export const wompi = new WompiClient({
  publicKey: process.env.WOMPI_PUBLIC_KEY!,
  privateKey: process.env.WOMPI_PRIVATE_KEY,
  sandbox: true,
});`;

const acceptanceSnippet = `const [merchantError, merchant] = await wompi.merchants.getMerchant();
if (merchantError) throw merchantError;

const acceptanceToken = merchant.data.presigned_acceptance?.acceptance_token;
if (!acceptanceToken) throw new Error("Merchant has no acceptance token");`;

const tokenSnippet = `const [tokenError, token] = await wompi.tokens.tokenizeCard({
  number: "4242424242424242",
  cvc: "123",
  exp_month: "12",
  exp_year: "29",
  card_holder: "PEDRO PEREZ",
});
if (tokenError) throw tokenError;

token.data.id; // cardToken_xxx — pass this into the transaction`;

const signatureSnippet = `import { getSignatureKey } from "@pulgueta/wompi/server";

const reference = \`order-\${Date.now()}\`;
const amountInCents = 2_490_000;

const signature = await getSignatureKey({
  reference,
  amountInCents,
  integrityKey: process.env.WOMPI_INTEGRITY_KEY!,
});`;

const transactionSnippet = `const [transactionError, transaction] = await wompi.transactions.createTransaction({
  acceptance_token: acceptanceToken,
  amount_in_cents: amountInCents,
  currency: "COP",
  signature,
  customer_email: "customer@example.com",
  reference,
  payment_method: { type: "CARD", token: token.data.id, installments: 1 },
});
if (transactionError) throw transactionError;

transaction.data.status; // "PENDING" — poll wompi.transactions.getTransaction(id)`;
---

<DocsLayout
  section="Getting Started"
  title="Quickstart"
  description="Charge a sandbox card end-to-end in five steps using only @pulgueta/wompi."
>
  <p>
    This walkthrough creates a working sandbox card charge. It assumes you've already
    <a href="/docs/installation">installed the SDK</a> and exported
    <code>WOMPI_PUBLIC_KEY</code>, <code>WOMPI_PRIVATE_KEY</code> and
    <code>WOMPI_INTEGRITY_KEY</code>.
  </p>

  <Callout type="tip" title="Live demo">
    The same flow runs interactively in the <a href="/docs/examples/card-checkout">card checkout
      example</a>. Open that page in another tab if you want to compare requests and responses
    while you read.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="1-instantiate-the-client">1. Instantiate the client</h2>
  <p>
    Create the client once and reuse it. <code>sandbox: true</code> sends requests to
    <code>https://api-sandbox.co.uat.wompi.dev</code>; set it to <code>false</code> for production.
  </p>

  <CodeBlock code={clientSnippet} lang="ts" filename="lib/wompi.ts" />

  <h2 id="2-fetch-the-acceptance-token">2. Fetch the acceptance token</h2>
  <p>
    Every transaction must include the merchant's presigned acceptance token — proof that the
    customer accepted the merchant's policies. Fetch it from the merchant endpoint.
  </p>

  <CodeBlock code={acceptanceSnippet} lang="ts" />

  <h2 id="3-tokenize-the-card">3. Tokenize the card</h2>
  <p>
    The raw card number never touches the transaction call. Tokenize first; pass the resulting
    token id into the transaction body.
  </p>

  <CodeBlock code={tokenSnippet} lang="ts" />

  <Callout type="note" title="Test cards">
    In sandbox, the card number <code>4242 4242 4242 4242</code> is approved and
    <code>4111 1111 1111 1111</code> is declined. See the
    <a href="https://docs.wompi.co/docs/colombia/widget-checkout-web/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Wompi test cards reference</a
    > for the full list.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="4-sign-the-amount">4. Sign the amount</h2>
  <p>
    Wompi requires an SHA-256 signature over the reference, amount and currency, salted with your
    integrity key. <code>getSignatureKey</code> from the <code>/server</code> entry computes it for
    you.
  </p>

  <CodeBlock code={signatureSnippet} lang="ts" />

  <p>
    Read <a href="/docs/integrity-signature">Integrity signature</a> for the full rules — including
    when to include <code>expiration_time</code>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="5-create-the-transaction">5. Create the transaction</h2>
  <p>
    Stitch it together: the acceptance token, the signed amount, the card token, the reference and
    a customer email. The response status starts at <code>PENDING</code> — poll
    <code>getTransaction(id)</code> until it resolves.
  </p>

  <CodeBlock code={transactionSnippet} lang="ts" />

  <h2 id="what-next">What next</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/docs/error-handling">Error handling</a> — branch on
      <code>error.type</code> to differentiate validation, not-found and HTTP errors.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/docs/payment-links">Payment links</a> — skip card tokenization entirely and hand
      the customer a hosted checkout URL.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/docs/examples/card-checkout">Card checkout example</a> — the same flow, but as a
      live Astro API route you can read and copy.
    </li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
